episodes.title: L-Animals
episodes.plot: From lonely whales to larval locomotives, Stephen Fry takes a look at the animal kingdom themed around the letter L. With Sarah Millican, Ross Noble, Colin Lane and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Location, Location, Location
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry goes on location in the company of Jason Manford, Aisling Bea, Johnny Vegas and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Literature
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry looks into literature and language. With Lloyd Langford, Victoria Coren Mitchell, Jack Whitehall and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Levity
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry looks at levity, levitation and lights with Josh Widdicombe, Sue Perkins, Frank Skinner and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Lenses
episodes.plot: Panel quiz. Stephen Fry considers lenses, lungs, legs and other parts of the body beginning with L. With Jo Brand, Josh Widdicombe, Phill Jupitus and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Liblabble
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry looks through a list of L-themed larks - a 'liblabble'. The Reverend Richard Coles, Sara Pascoe, Bill Bailey and Alan Davies are on the panel.

episodes.title: Lethal
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry looks at the quite interesting side of all things lethal, with a deadly and dangerous panel of Bill Bailey, Sandi Toksvig, Jason Manford and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Lovely
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry looks into love and loveliness with Josh Widdicombe, Aisling Bea, Tony Hawks and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Ladies and Gents
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry hosts the quiz show in which the aim is to be interesting. The ladies and gents on the panel are Ross Noble, Kathy Lette, Sue Perkins and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Lying
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry seeks out the truth about liars and lying with Sara Pascoe, Jack Whitehall, Adam Hills and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Lumped Together
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry lumps together a whole lot of L-themed larks, from lava lamps to love handles. With David Mitchell, Ronni Ancona, Jimmy Carr, and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: No-L
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry introduces the QI Christmas special - and a very special guest. With Carrie Fisher, Bill Bailey, Jimmy Carr and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Lucky Losers
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry takes a quite interesting look at luck and loss. Jeremy Clarkson, Sandi Toksvig, Danny Baker and Alan Davies are the panel hoping to be fortunate enough to avoid failure.

episodes.title: Little and Large
episodes.plot: Quiz show. Stephen Fry looks at the multi-sized world of the little and the large. With Richard Osman, Lucy Porter, Phill Jupitus and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Long Lost
episodes.plot: Quiz show in which the aim is to be interesting. At long last, it is Stephen Fry and the QI Long Lost show. With Suggs, Claudia O'Doherty, Jimmy Carr and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Landmarks
episodes.plot: Where is the Duchy of Cornwall? What does a cowboy call his rope? These are amongst the quite interesting questions host Stephen Fry will put to his guests Jo Brand, Colin Lane, David Mitchell and Alan Davies on the topic of landmarks.

episodes.title: VG Part One
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry and Alan Davies are joined by a selection of guests for a compilation of favourite moments from the L series.

episodes.title: VG Part Two
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry and Alan Davies are joined by a selection of guests for a compilation of favourite moments from the L series.
